title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 4/29/09 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




April 29, 2009

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 4/29/09




THE WHITE HOUSE   Office of the Press Secretary  ______________________________________________________________________  FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                                               April 29, 2009  NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE:   Kevin W. Concannon, of Maine, to be Under Secretary of Agriculture for Food, Nutrition, and Consumer Services, vice Nancy Montanez-Johner, resigned.   Robert M. Groves, of Michigan, to be Director of the Census, vice Steven H. Murdock, resigned.
